miscConds.notes:
Prison sentence stayed on condition you immediately enter into the Dunn County TAD Program;
Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;
No possession or consumption of any controlled substance without a valid prescription;
No possession or consumption of alcohol;
No entrance into bars or taverns without advanced written permission of Probation & Parole;
Cooperate with any assessment or treatment as required by Probation & Parole;
Complete 200 hours of community service within the first year of probation with probation supervising and give credit for community service hours completed through the TAD program in Dunn County; 
Sign any releases in favor of the District Attorney's Office for sharing information on his performance while on probation;
Pay all court order obligations.
